Q: In C#, how to define a property that accept parameters or a function that return reference as in C++? A: <p>Using <em>corrected</em> solution of Charlieface, the full solution of indexer of level 2 is following.</p>
<pre class="lang-cs prettyprint-override"><code>public UInt32 this[int iFrom, int iTo]
{
    get
    {
        int iShiftLeft = 8 * sizeof(UInt32) - iFrom;
        int iShiftRight = iShiftLeft + iTo;
        return (this.iValue &lt;&lt; iShiftLeft) &gt;&gt; iShiftRight;
    }
    set
    {
        UInt32 nLeftValue = (iValue &gt;&gt; iFrom) &lt;&lt; iFrom;
        UInt32 nRightValue = 0;
        if (iTo &gt; 0)
        {
            int iShift = 8 * sizeof(UInt32) - iTo;
            nRightValue = (iValue &lt;&lt; iShift) &gt;&gt; iShift;
        }
        this.iValue = nLeftValue + (value &lt;&lt; iTo) + nRightValue;
    }
}
</code></pre>
<p>Pseudocode of euclidian division algorithm found on <a href="https://fr.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Division" rel="nofollow noreferrer">https://fr.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Division</a> is currently (2025-12-24) following</p>
